				\begin{document}$$\eta_{STH}\left(\%\right)=\frac{Rate\;of\;H_{2\;}production\times\Delta G_{H2+O2=H2O}}{P_{in}}\times100=\frac{J\times1.23V}{P_{in}}\times100$$\end{document}where J is the total current density for PEC Li extraction caused by all ion transportation (mA cm−2, Fig. 5a). In the first stage, J was 0.22 mA cm−2. It can reach 1.43 and 2.96 mA cm−2 in the second and third stages, respectively (Figure S8). Correspondingly, the ηSTH improved from 0.27 to 3.65%.

